{{Quote|Who would have thought the Yuuzhan Vong were another group of superweapon aficionados?|[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Traest Kre'fey]]|<ref name="The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth">''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory II: Rebirth]]''</ref>}}
The '''gravitic superweapon''' was a "[[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]]" that [[Kyp Durron]] claimed the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] were growing at the [[shipwomb]] in the remains of [[Sernpidal/Legends|Sernpidal]].

==History==
Claiming that it had the power to pull objects from thousands of [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] away, and presenting a [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]] of the supposed weapon drawing matter from [[Julevia|Sernpidal's sun]], Durron used [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] to take the information to [[General/Legends|General]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Traest Kre'fey]], hoping that they would help him destroy it. In truth, what they had seen was actually a [[dovin basal]] relay system used to provide [[Helium/Legends|helium]] and [[Hydrogen/Legends|hydrogen]] to what the Yuuzhan Vong were really growing at Sernpidal&mdash;a civilian [[Koros-Strohna|worldship]]. Kre'fey, Antilles, and Solo only realized this after they [[Second Battle of Sernpidal|attacked and destroyed]] the worldship.

